Mon Aug 21 17:46:55 UTC 2006  Ossama Othman  <ossama_othman at symantec dot com>

        * ace/Numeric_Limits.h (ACE_Numeric_Limits):

          The Microsoft Platform SDK does not provide
          std::numeric_limits<> specializations for 64 bit integers so we
          need to explicitly provide ACE_Numeric_Limits<> specializations
          to compensate for this deficiency.  [Bug 2639]

          Unfortunately there is no way to tell if the platform SDK is
          being used so we specialize for the ACE_WIN64 + MSVC++ 7.1 case,
          which is the configuration that exhibits this problem.  It also
          happens to be a fairly isolated configuration since 64-bit
          support in MSVC++ 7.1 was not very good to begin with.

