          numeric_limits::min/max() traits.  Prevent those macros from
          being defined by defining the Windows-specific NOMINMAX symbol
          before any Windows headers are included.  This is currently
          only done for Mingw builds since the problem is not exhibited by
          other Windows builds (e.g. MSVC++, Borland, etc).

